article.headline: Drake 17, Upper Iowa 13
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Cole Ingle threw an 8-yard touchdown pass to Zach Brower and Andrew Asbell returned a fumble 12 yards for a touchdown as Drake beat Upper Iowa 17-13 in the season opener for both teams Thursday. Ingle completed 18 of 31 passes for 149 yards. The Bulldogs were held to just 69 yards rushing by the Peacock defense. Dominique Jackson scored Upper Iowa's only touchdown on an 89-yard punt return in the second quarter. Ben Curran was 18-for-31 for 130 yards for the Peacocks.
